"title": "6723: redemption, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6723",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The culmination of the OT work of redemption is seen in the cross of Jesus Christ, by which believers are liberated from bondage to sin.</p>\n<h2>Redemption is achieved through Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's teaching on redemption</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:25\">MRK 14:22–14:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:20-Luke22:22\">LUK 22:20–22:22</a></p>\n<h2>Apostolic teaching on redemption</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the redemption of believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:6\">1TI 2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Redemption comes through the shedding of the blood of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:23\">1CO 7:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:23-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:23–11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5-Rev1:6\">REV 1:5–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></p>\n<h2>The results of redemption</h2>\n<h3>Forgiveness of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13-Col1:14\">COL 1:13–1:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Justification and freedom from the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:8-Gal3:10\">GAL 3:8–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23-Rom3:25\">ROM 3:23–3:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:5\">GAL 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Inclusion in the covenant</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14\">GAL 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a></p>\n<h3>Freedom to live a new life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:4–4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:19–6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:22-1Cor7:24\">1CO 7:22–7:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13\">COL 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5-Rev1:6\">REV 1:5–1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></p>\n<h2>Creation and believers await final redemption</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:19-Rom8:23\">ROM 8:19–8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:28\">LUK 21:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:21\">ACT 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:14\">EPH 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a></p>",
